Benjamin Button,
this is my husband, Robert.

1677
02:25:52,972 --> 02:25:55,372
- How do you do?
- A pleasure.

1678
02:26:03,516 --> 02:26:06,508
Well, it was very nice to meet you.

1679
02:26:06,619 --> 02:26:08,416
- We'll be in the car, darling.
- All right.

1680
02:26:08,521 --> 02:26:09,647
Bye.

1681
02:26:10,390 --> 02:26:12,153
I'm just locking up.

1682
02:26:16,929 --> 02:26:17,987
Wow.

1683
02:26:20,533 --> 02:26:23,400
She's beautiful. Like her mother.

1684
02:26:25,004 --> 02:26:27,472
- Does she dance?
- Not very well.

1685
02:26:27,573 --> 02:26:29,473
I guess that'd be
from my side of things.

1686
02:26:29,575 --> 02:26:31,565
She's a dear, sweet girl.

1687
02:26:32,778 --> 02:26:37,112
She seems a little lost.
But then, who isn't at 12?

1688
02:26:37,316 --> 02:26:41,548
A lot of her reminds me of you.

1689
02:26:42,454 --> 02:26:46,390
My husband, he's a widower, or was...
Was a widower.

1690
02:26:46,792 --> 02:26:50,694
He's an incredibly kind, just bright,
adventurous man.

1691
02:26:53,865 --> 02:26:56,561
- He's been a terrific father.
- Good.

1692
02:27:01,273 --> 02:27:05,175
- You are so much younger.
- Only on the outside.

1693
02:27:07,279 --> 02:27:08,803
You were right.

1694
02:27:10,582 --> 02:27:13,949
I couldn't have been raising both of you.

1695
02:27:14,052 --> 02:27:15,814
I'm not that strong.

1696
02:27:20,024 --> 02:27:22,049
So, where are you staying?

1697
02:27:24,729 --> 02:27:25,718
What are you gonna do?

1698
02:27:25,830 --> 02:27:29,630
I'm staying at the Pontchartrain Hotel
on the Avenue.

1699
02:27:29,734 --> 02:27:33,261
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

1700
02:27:33,371 --> 02:27:34,531
But...

1701
02:27:41,045 --> 02:27:42,672
They're waiting.

1702
02:28:24,821 --> 02:28:28,086
I remember that. That was him?

1703
02:28:30,760 --> 02:28:31,920
The hurricane has changed directions.

1704
02:28:32,028 --> 02:28:33,859
It's going to make landfall
sometime soon.

1705
02:28:33,963 --> 02:28:35,692
- Am I supposed to do something?
- Arrangements are being made

1706
02:28:35,799 --> 02:28:37,027
to move people, but it's up to you.

1707
02:28:37,133 --> 02:28:38,998
No. No, we're... We're staying.

1708
02:28:39,102 --> 02:28:41,730
I'll let you know if anything changes.

1709
02:28:43,772 --> 02:28:48,106
"That night, while I was sitting
and wondering why I came back at all,

1710
02:28:48,210 --> 02:28:50,542
"there was a knock at the door. "

1711
02:28:54,183 --> 02:28:55,411
Come in.

1712
02:29:09,731 --> 02:29:11,392
Are you all right?

1713
02:29:14,503 --> 02:29:18,599
I'm sorry,
I don't know what I'm doing here.

1714
02:29:27,649 --> 02:29:29,138
Nothing lasts.

1715
02:29:32,620 --> 02:29:34,952
I have never stopped loving you.

1716
02:29:40,962 --> 02:29:43,658
Oh, but, Benjamin,
I'm an old woman now.

1717
02:29:54,308 --> 02:29:56,503
Some things you never forget.

1718
02:30:16,796 --> 02:30:17,854
<i>...so few people even know</i>

1719
02:30:17,964 --> 02:30:19,659
<i>that you were ever in jail
in the first place.</i>

1720
02:30:19,766 --> 02:30:21,961
<i>I'll tell you, I am sick about it, too,</i>

1721
02:30:22,068 --> 02:30:24,628
<i>because, please,
if they're not gonna give you an award</i>

1722
02:30:24,738 --> 02:30:26,797
<i>like "Man of the Year,"
at least what they could do</i>

1723
02:30:26,907 --> 02:30:29,569
<i>is stop having you listed
as an ex-convict</i>

1724
02:30:29,676 --> 02:30:32,167
<i>which I think is, again, so unfair.</i>

1725
02:30:44,958 --> 02:30:46,755
Good night, Benjamin.

1726
02:30:48,295 --> 02:30:49,956
Good night, Daisy.

1727
02:30:53,166 --> 02:30:57,397
<i>And as I knew I would,
I watched her go.</i>

1728
02:31:00,139 --> 02:31:02,437
That's the last thing he wrote.

1729
02:31:03,609 --> 02:31:08,171
Sometime after your father passed,

1730
02:31:08,280 --> 02:31:11,113
there was a call.

1731
02:31:14,186 --> 02:31:15,346
Hello.

1732
02:31:16,455 --> 02:31:17,945
Yes, speaking.

1733
02:31:21,293 --> 02:31:23,784
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

1734
02:31:33,639 --> 02:31:35,504
It's the corner house.

1735
02:31:57,695 --> 02:31:59,060
Come on in.

1736
02:32:04,669 --> 02:32:06,694
- I'm Daisy Fuller.
- I'm David Hernandez,

1737
02:32:06,804 --> 02:32:10,501
with the Orleans Parish Department
of Child Welfare Services.

1738
02:32:10,608 --> 02:32:13,236
He was living in a condemned building.

1739
02:32:15,046 --> 02:32:17,344
The police found this with him.

1740
02:32:17,448 --> 02:32:20,383
This address.
It's got your name in it a lot.

1741
02:32:21,586 --> 02:32:24,214
He's in very poor health.
He was taken to the hospital.

1742
02:32:24,322 --> 02:32:28,348
He doesn't seem to know who
or where he is. He's very confused.

1743
02:32:28,458 --> 02:32:32,019
I was telling Mr. Hernandez
that Benjamin is one of us.

1744
02:32:32,129 --> 02:32:35,963
If he needs a place to stay,
it's all right, he can stay here.

1745
02:33:05,429 --> 02:33:06,691
Benjamin?

1746
02:33:10,567 --> 02:33:12,363
You play beautifully.

1747
02:33:15,871 --> 02:33:17,702
He doesn't seem to like to be touched.

1748
02:33:17,807 --> 02:33:19,468
He goes in and out
of states of recognition.

1749
02:33:19,575 --> 02:33:21,202
The doctors say,
if they didn't know any better,

1750
02:33:21,310 --> 02:33:23,744
he has the beginnings of dementia.

1751
02:33:25,548 --> 02:33:27,277
Do you remember me?

1752
02:33:30,453 --> 02:33:31,784
I'm Daisy.

1753
02:33:34,390 --> 02:33:35,857
I'm Benjamin.

1754
02:33:41,564 --> 02:33:44,226
It's nice to meet you, Benjamin.

1755
02:33:45,935 --> 02:33:51,305
Would you mind if I sit with you?
I would love to hear you play.

1756
02:33:55,177 --> 02:33:56,666
Do I know you?

1757
02:34:01,649 --> 02:34:03,276
<i>- I want some breakfast.
- And every day,</i>

1758
02:34:03,384 --> 02:34:07,343
<i>I would stop by to make sure
that he was comfortable.</i>

1759
02:34:07,455 --> 02:34:10,083
- No, I didn't.
- You just finished eating.

1760
02:34:10,191 --> 02:34:12,523
Don't think I don't know
what you're doing!

1761
02:34:12,627 --> 02:34:15,357
You're all fucking liars!

1762
02:34:15,463 --> 02:34:18,388
He doesn't believe
he just had his breakfast.

1763
02:34:19,701 --> 02:34:23,330
Now, why don't we see

1764
02:34:23,438 --> 02:34:26,805
if we can't find something else
for you to do?

1765
02:34:26,975 --> 02:34:30,138
I have a feeling
there's a lot of things I can't remember.

1766
02:34:30,245 --> 02:34:32,145
Well, like what, sugar?

1767
02:34:33,414 --> 02:34:37,407
It's like there's this whole life I had,

1768
02:34:38,887 --> 02:34:41,286
and I can't remember what it was.

1769
02:34:44,091 --> 02:34:45,422
It's okay.

1770
02:34:47,528 --> 02:34:48,995
It's okay to forget things.

1771
02:34:49,229 --> 02:34:54,792
<i>Many times, he would simply forget
who or where he was.</i>

1772
02:34:55,135 --> 02:34:56,796
There he is, he's up there on the roof.

1773
02:34:56,904 --> 02:34:58,599
<i>It wasn't easy.</i>

1774
02:34:58,705 --> 02:35:00,935
- Benjamin!
- I can see everything!

1775
02:35:01,041 --> 02:35:02,804
- I can see the big river!
- That's right,

1776
02:35:02,910 --> 02:35:04,639
you can see everything, sweetheart.

1777
02:35:04,745 --> 02:35:06,736
I can see the graveyard
where Mama's buried,

1778
02:35:06,847 --> 02:35:10,214
- and all those other people.
- I want you to come down!

1779
02:35:10,317 --> 02:35:14,048
- What if I could fly?
- I knew a man who could fly.

1780
02:35:15,055 --> 02:35:18,024
You come down
and I'll tell you all about him.

1781
02:35:21,595 --> 02:35:23,187
Somebody go up there.

1782
02:35:29,802 --> 02:35:32,771
<i>He was five when I moved in.</i>

1783
02:35:32,872 --> 02:35:37,332
<i>Nearly the same age I was
when I had met him.</i>

1784
02:35:43,349 --> 02:35:47,285
"This is the picture
of Old Man Kangaroo

1785
02:35:47,386 --> 02:35:49,820
"at 5:00 in the afternoon

1786
02:35:49,922 --> 02:35:53,380
"when he had got
his beautiful hind legs. "

1787
02:35:54,627 --> 02:35:55,924
<i>The days passed.</i>

1788
02:35:56,028 --> 02:36:00,260
<i>And I watched as he forgot how to walk</i>

1789
02:36:05,504 --> 02:36:07,938
<i>- and how to talk.
- What's my name?</i>

1790
02:36:08,407 --> 02:36:09,737
I'm Daisy.

1791
02:36:10,909 --> 02:36:12,672
Can you say "Daisy"?

1792
02:36:14,246 --> 02:36:19,513
<i>In 2002, they put up a new clock
in that train station.</i>

1793
02:36:26,358 --> 02:36:30,124
<i>And in the spring of 2003,</i>

1794
02:36:34,499 --> 02:36:36,160
<i>he looked at me</i>

1795
02:36:38,670 --> 02:36:43,733
<i>and I knew that he knew who I was.</i>

1796
02:36:47,279 --> 02:36:53,081
<i>And then he closed his eyes
as if to go to sleep.</i>

1797
02:37:25,649 --> 02:37:29,813
- I wish I'd known him.
- Now you do.

1798
02:37:34,325 --> 02:37:38,090
Mom, I think I should go see
what's going on.

1799
02:37:45,134 --> 02:37:47,159
Good night, Benjamin.

1800
02:38:09,559 --> 02:38:11,925
<i>We're expecting flash flooding
after the levee break.</i>

1801
02:38:12,028 --> 02:38:14,258
<i>It occurred in the Ninth Ward.</i>

1802
02:38:17,300 --> 02:38:20,133
<i>Some people are born to sit by a river.</i>

1803
02:38:21,671 --> 02:38:23,604
<i>Some get struck by lightning.</i>

1804
02:38:25,507 --> 02:38:27,600
<i>Some have an ear for music.</i>

1805
02:38:29,211 --> 02:38:30,838
<i>Some are artists.</i>

1806
02:38:32,180 --> 02:38:33,511
<i>Some swim.</i>

1807
02:38:34,950 --> 02:38:36,577
<i>Some know buttons.</i>

1808
02:38:38,387 --> 02:38:39,752
<i>Some know Shakespeare.</i>

1809
02:38:40,922 --> 02:38:42,685
<i>Some are mothers.</i>

1810
02:38:44,659 --> 02:38:47,685
<i>And some people dance.</i>

